<org.eclipse.epf.uma:PracticeDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-0dp7WhAofO8o4DsLvECnBA" name="uam_deconflict_needs,_yJz1QNEKEdyC2cfK_t2EKQ" guid="-0dp7WhAofO8o4DsLvECnBA" authors="DW Enstrom" changeDate="2015-10-14T14:22:39.507-0400" version="2.0.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;XE_Best_Practices__Deconflict_Requirements&quot; name=&quot;XE_Best_Practices__Deconflict_Requirements&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;table bordercolor=&quot;#ffffff&quot; width=&quot;90%&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;23%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;h3 dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
                    Introduction&#xD;
                &lt;/h3>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    Stakeholders are people too, which have differing views colored by personal experience, biases and&#xD;
                    knowledge. This cannot be ignored when&amp;#160;gathering business requirements. Balancing various&#xD;
                    perspectives and opinions and arriving at a consensus is required.&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;4%&quot;>&#xD;
                &amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;63%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;table bordercolor=&quot;#000000&quot; cellpadding=&quot;5&quot; width=&quot;99%&quot; border=&quot;3&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
                        &lt;tr>&#xD;
                            &lt;td width=&quot;16%&quot;>&#xD;
                                &lt;strong>Benefits&lt;/strong>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                            &lt;td width=&quot;64%&quot;>&#xD;
                                &lt;ul>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        A single agreed set of requirements&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Reduced rehash, rework, and misunderstandings&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Optimized business value&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                &lt;/ul>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
                        &lt;tr>&#xD;
                            &lt;td>&#xD;
                                &lt;strong>Pattern&lt;/strong>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                            &lt;td>&#xD;
                                &lt;ul>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Clarify and validate requirements from multiple sources&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        De-conflict differing views&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Have an issue escalation process for requirements and solutions (and keep an&#xD;
                                        electronic record of these in an easy to retrieve environment)&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Define a single stakeholder representative responsible for the final decision on&#xD;
                                        requirements&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Manage requirements and changes to them&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Use the same approach as above to manage design decisions affecting the business&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                &lt;/ul>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
                        &lt;tr>&#xD;
                            &lt;td>&#xD;
                                &lt;strong>Anti-Patterns&lt;/strong>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                            &lt;td>&#xD;
                                &lt;ul>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Force stakeholder acceptance of requirements&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        No requirements deconfliction process&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Small or biased stakeholder representation&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                &lt;/ul>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
                    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
                &lt;/table>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
&lt;/table>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Discussion&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This principle could be viewed as an IT architecture variation of “balancing competing stakeholder priorities”. But it&#xD;
    addresses the practical side of stakeholder involvement, even if it is a stakeholder responsible for helping define&#xD;
    business requirements or a technical stakeholder helping to define the technical view of the system. Requirements are&#xD;
    managed and deconflicted—the end result will only be as good as the input received. Therefore, it is best to have&#xD;
    multiple sources for stakeholder input and to have a deconfliction mechanism if a consensus cannot be reached. “&lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../UAM/guidances/practices/uam_do_the_math_C1C555B6.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_8ld5QECkEeOfR_FtRm9PUg&quot;>Do the Math&lt;/a>” can often help to de-conflict—suggested solutions may not be as&#xD;
    attractive once one works through the numbers.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:PracticeDescription>
